{"title_page": "Mahindra Quanto", "text_new": "{{Infobox automobile\n| image = Mahindra Quanto image.JPG\n| name = Mahindra Quanto\n| manufacturer = [[Mahindra & Mahindra Limited]]\n| assembly = [[Nasik]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]\n| aka = Mahindra NuvoSport (facelift)\n| production = 2012\u20132018\n| class = [[Mini SUV]]\n| body_style = 5-door [[SUV]]\n| layout = [[Front-engine design|Front-engine]], [[rear-wheel drive]]<br>[[Front-engine design|Front-engine]], [[four-wheel drive]]\n| engine = 1.5L ''mHawk'' [[Straight-3|I3]] [[diesel engine|diesel]]<br />2.2L ''[[PSA_EW/DW_engine#DW12|DW12 mHawk]]'' [[Straight-4|I4]] [[diesel engine|diesel]]<ref>[https://www.sicurauto.it/news/mahindra-quanto-22-d-4wd-120-cv-prova-su-strada.html Mahindra Quanto in Italy]</ref>\n| transmission = 5-speed [[manual transmission|manual]]\n| wheelbase = {{convert|2760|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| length = {{convert|3985|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| width = {{convert|1850|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| height = {{convert|1880|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| weight = {{convert|1640|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}}\n| related = [[Mahindra TUV300]]\n| model_years = 2012\u20132016 (Quanto)<br/>2016\u20132018 (NuvoSport)\n}}\nThe '''Mahindra Quanto''' was a 7-seater [[mini sport utility vehicle|mini SUV]] designed and manufactured by the Indian automaker [[Mahindra & Mahindra Limited|Mahindra & Mahindra]]. Since 2016, the facelifted version of the Quanto was marketed as the '''Mahindra NuvoSport'''.\n\n==Specification==\n\nThe Quanto is powered by a 1.5-litre mHawk three-cylinder 12-valve turbo diesel engine known as MCR100, and produces {{convert|98.6|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on}} at 3,750 rpm and develops {{convert|240|Nm|lb.ft|0|abbr=on}} of torque at 1,600-2,800 rpm.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mahindra Quanto Review|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/features/smartbuy/automobiles/mahindra-quanto-review/article4002171.ece|work=The Hindu|accessdate=30 November 2012}}</ref> It accelerates from 0 to 100 kmh(60&nbsp;mph) in 16\u201317 seconds.\n\nThe Quanto is offered in four trim levels: C2, C4, C6 and C8. All models share the same diesel engine. Since the release, 1,782 units were sold in September. In October, sales were exceeded to 2,497 units. At the end of November, 2,297 units were sold.\n\n==Variants <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cartrade.com/mahindra-cars/quanto|title=Mahindra Quanto in India - Price, Mileage, Reviews, Images, Specs|author=Staff|publisher=cartrade.com|date=2015-08-11}}</ref>==\n<div >\n{|class=\"wikitable\" cellpadding=\"0\"  cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width: 50%;\"\n\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 40%;\" COLSPAN =\"2\"| VERSION\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 30%;\" | MILEAGE\n! scope=\"col\" | PRICE\n|----\n| rowspan=\"4\" |'''DIESEL'''\n\n|Quanto C2 1493 cc <br />Manual\n|City: 15 kmpl <br />Highway: 17 kmpl\n|Rs 6.48 lakhs <br />Ex-showroom, Mumbai\n|----\n|Quanto C4 1493 cc <br />Manual\n|City: 15 kmpl <br />Highway: 17 kmpl\n|Rs 7.02 lakhs <br />Ex-showroom, Mumbai\n|----\n|Quanto C6 1493 cc <br />Manual\n|City: 15 kmpl <br />Highway: 17 kmpl\n|Rs 7.48 lakhs <br />Ex-showroom, Mumbai\n|----\n|Quanto C8 1493 cc <br />Manual\n|City: 15 kmpl <br />Highway: 17 kmpl\n|Rs 7.98 lakhs <br />Ex-showroom, Mumbai\n|----\n|}\n\n</div>\n\n== NuvoSport (2016-2018) ==\nThe Mahindra NuvoSport is the continuation and facelifted version of the Quanto, it was launched in April 4, 2016. The NuvoSport features a much different exterior design than the Quanto, but however, the interior design remains unchanged, apart from the added interior features. It is still powered by the same 1.5-litre mHawk turbo diesel engine as the previous Quanto.\n\nIn 2018, the NuvoSport has been discontinued due to slow sales.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|http://www.mahindraquanto.com/}}\n\n{{Mahindra and Mahindra vehicles}}\n\n[[Category:Mahindra vehicles|Quanto]]\n[[Category:Cars introduced in 2012]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox automobile\n| image = Mahindra Quanto image.JPG\n| name = Mahindra Quanto\n| manufacturer = [[Mahindra & Mahindra Limited]]\n| assembly = [[Nasik]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]\n| aka = Mahindra NuvoSport (facelift)\n| production = 2012\u20132018\n| class = [[Mini SUV]]\n| body_style = 5-door [[SUV]]\n| layout = [[Front-engine design|Front-engine]], [[rear-wheel drive]]<br>[[Front-engine design|Front-engine]], [[four-wheel drive]]\n| engine = 1.5L ''mHawk'' [[Straight-3|I3]] [[diesel engine|diesel]]<br />2.2L ''[[PSA_EW/DW_engine#DW12|DW12 mHawk]]'' [[Straight-4|I4]] [[diesel engine|diesel]]<ref>[https://www.sicurauto.it/news/mahindra-quanto-22-d-4wd-120-cv-prova-su-strada.html Mahindra Quanto in Italy]</ref>\n| transmission = 5-speed [[manual transmission|manual]]\n| wheelbase = {{convert|2760|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| length = {{convert|3985|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| width = {{convert|1850|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| height = {{convert|1880|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| weight = {{convert|1640|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}}\n| related = [[Mahindra TUV300]]\n| model_years = 2012\u20132016 (Quanto)<br/>2016\u20132018 (NuvoSport)\n}}\nThe '''Mahindra Quanto''' was a 7-seater [[mini sport utility vehicle|mini SUV]] designed and manufactured by the Indian automaker [[Mahindra & Mahindra Limited|Mahindra & Mahindra]]. Since 2016, the facelifted version of the Quanto was marketed as the '''Mahindra NuvoSport'''.\n\n==Specification==\n\nThe Quanto is powered by a 1.5-litre mHawk three-cylinder 12-valve turbo diesel engine known as MCR100, and produces {{convert|98.6|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on}} at 3,750 rpm and develops {{convert|240|Nm|lb.ft|0|abbr=on}} of torque at 1,600-2,800 rpm.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mahindra Quanto Review|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/features/smartbuy/automobiles/mahindra-quanto-review/article4002171.ece|work=The Hindu|accessdate=30 November 2012}}</ref> It accelerates from 0 to 100 kmh(60&nbsp;mph) in 16\u201317 seconds.\n\nThe Quanto is offered in four trim levels: C2, C4, C6 and C8. All models share the same diesel engine. Since the release, 1,782 units were sold in September. In October, sales were exceeded to 2,497 units. At the end of November, 2,297 units were sold.\n\n==Variants <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cartrade.com/mahindra-cars/quanto|title=Mahindra Quanto in India - Price, Mileage, Reviews, Images, Specs|author=Staff|publisher=cartrade.com|date=2015-08-11}}</ref>==\n<div >\n{|class=\"wikitable\" cellpadding=\"0\"  cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width: 50%;\"\n\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 40%;\" COLSPAN =\"2\"| VERSION\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 30%;\" | MILEAGE\n! scope=\"col\" | PRICE\n|----\n| rowspan=\"4\" |'''DIESEL'''\n\n|Quanto C2 1493 cc <br />Manual\n|City: 15 kmpl <br />Highway: 17 kmpl\n|Rs 6.48 lakhs <br />Ex-showroom, Mumbai\n|----\n|Quanto C4 1493 cc <br />Manual\n|City: 15 kmpl <br />Highway: 17 kmpl\n|Rs 7.02 lakhs <br />Ex-showroom, Mumbai\n|----\n|Quanto C6 1493 cc <br />Manual\n|City: 15 kmpl <br />Highway: 17 kmpl\n|Rs 7.48 lakhs <br />Ex-showroom, Mumbai\n|----\n|Quanto C8 1493 cc <br />Manual\n|City: 15 kmpl <br />Highway: 17 kmpl\n|Rs 7.98 lakhs <br />Ex-showroom, Mumbai\n|----\n|}\n\n</div>\n\n== NuvoSport (2016-2018) ==\nThe Mahindra NuvoSport is the continuation and facelifted version of the Quanto, it was launched in April 4, 2016. The NuvoSport features a much different exterior design than the Quanto, but however, the interior design remains unchanged, apart from the added interior features. It is still powered by the same 1.5-litre mHawk turbo diesel engine as the previous Quanto.\n\nIn 2018, the NuvoSport has been discontinued due to slow sales.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|http://www.mahindraquanto.com/}}\n\n{{Mahindra and Mahindra vehicles}}\n\n[[Category:Mahindra vehicles|Quanto]]\n[[Category:Cars introduced in 2012]]\n[[Category:2010s cars]]\n", "name_user": "TKOIII", "label": "safe", "comment": "Removed redundant category as per WP:Subcat. Parent category not needed when one of its subcategories